\begin{document}

\section*{Problem}

An electric bell has a frequency of 100 Hz. If its time constant is 2 s, determine the \( Q \) factor for the bell.

\section*{Solution}

The \( Q \) factor, or quality factor, of a resonant system is given by the formula:

\[
Q = 2 \pi f \tau
\]

where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \( f \) is the frequency of the system,
    \item \( \tau \) is the time constant.
\end{itemize}

Given:
\[
f = 100 \, \text{Hz}, \quad \tau = 2 \, \text{s}
\]

Substituting these values into the formula, we have:

\[
Q = 2 \pi \times 100 \, \text{Hz} \times 2 \, \text{s}
\]

\[
Q = 400 \pi
\]

Thus, the \( Q \) factor for the bell is \( 400 \pi \).

\end{document}

