        \item Stage 2  a process by which its volume remains constant, its pressure returns to its original value and $10^4 \, \text{J}$ of heat is added to the system.
        \item Stage 3  an isobaric compression to its original volume, with $3 \times 10^4 \, \text{J}$ of heat being removed from the system.
    \end{enumerate}
