\]

The power dissipated in the $5\,\Omega$ resistor is:

\[
P_{5\Omega} = I_{5\Omega}^2 \times 5\,\Omega = \left(\frac{12}{31}\right)^2 \times 5\,\Omega = \frac{144}{961} \times 5\,\Omega = \frac{720}{961}\,\text{W}
\]

The power dissipated in the $2\,\Omega$ resistor is:

\[
P_{2\Omega} = I_{2\Omega}^2 \times 2\,\Omega = \left(\frac{30}{31}\right)^2 \times 2\,\Omega = \frac{900}{961} \times 2\,\Omega = \frac{1800}{961}\,\text{W}
\]

