\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{graphicx}

\begin{document}

\section*{Problem Statement}

As shown in Fig. 13.1, a beam of particles of charge $q$ enters a region where an electric field $\mathbf{E}$ is uniform and directed downwards. Its value is $80 \, \text{kV/m}$. Perpendicular to $\mathbf{E}$ and directed into the page is a magnetic field $\mathbf{B} = 0.4 \, \text{T}$.

\begin{enumerate}
    \item[(i)] If the speed of the particles is properly chosen, the particles will not be deflected by these crossed electric and magnetic fields. What speed is selected in this case?
    \item[(ii)] If the electric field is cut off and the same magnetic field is maintained, the charged particles move in the magnetic field in a circular path of radius $1.14 \, \text{cm}$. Determine the ratio of the electric charge to the mass of the particles.
\end{enumerate}

\begin{figure}[h]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{Fig13_1.png}
    \caption{Illustration of the problem setup.}
    \label{fig:13_1}
\end{figure}

\section*{Solution}

\subsection*{(i) Speed of the Particles}

For the particles to not be deflected by the crossed electric and magnetic fields, the electric force must equal the magnetic force:

\[
qE = qvB
\]

where:
- $E = 80 \times 10^3 \, \text{V/m}$
- $B = 0.4 \, \text{T}$

Solving for the speed $v$:

\[
v = \frac{E}{B} = \frac{80 \times 10^3 \, \text{V/m}}{0.4 \, \text{T}} = 2 \times 10^5 \, \text{m/s}
\]

\subsection*{(ii) Charge to Mass Ratio}

When the electric field is cut off, the particles move in a circular path due to the magnetic field. The centripetal force is provided by the magnetic force:

\[
qvB = \frac{mv^2}{r}
\]

Solving for the charge to mass ratio $\frac{q}{m}$:

\[
\frac{q}{m} = \frac{v}{Br}
\]

Given:
- $r = 1.14 \, \text{cm} = 0.0114 \, \text{m}$

Substituting the known values:

\[
\frac{q}{m} = \frac{2 \times 10^5 \, \text{m/s}}{0.4 \, \text{T} \times 0.0114 \, \text{m}} = \frac{2 \times 10^5}{0.00456} \approx 4.39 \times 10^7 \, \text{C/kg}
\]

\end{document}

