The force on this side (\(L = 10 \, \text{cm} = 0.1 \, \text{m}\)) is:
\[
F_2 = 5 \times 0.1 \times B_2
\]

\textbf{Forces on the sides perpendicular to the wire:}

The magnetic field is parallel to these sides, so the force is zero:
\[
F_3 = F_4 = 0
\]

\subsection*{(ii) Net Force on the Coil}

The net force on the coil is the vector sum of the forces on each segment. Since the forces on the perpendicular sides are zero, we only consider the parallel sides:

\[
F_{\text{net}} = F_1 - F_2
\]

Substitute the expressions for \(F_1\) and \(F_2\) to find the net force.

\end{document}

