\usepackage{siunitx}

\begin{document}

\section*{Problem}

A tuning circuit in a radio transmitter has a \SI{4e-6}{\henry} inductance in series with a \SI{5e-11}{\farad} capacitance. Find:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item the frequency of the waves transmitted.
    \item their wavelength.
\end{enumerate}

\section*{Solution}

\subsection*{(a) Frequency of the Waves Transmitted}

The resonant frequency \( f \) of an LC circuit is given by the formula:
\[
f = \frac{1}{2\pi \sqrt{LC}}
\]
where \( L = \SI{4e-6}{\henry} \) and \( C = \SI{5e-11}{\farad} \).

Substituting the given values:
\[
f = \frac{1}{2\pi \sqrt{(4 \times 10^{-6} \, \si{\henry})(5 \times 10^{-11} \, \si{\farad})}}
\]

Calculating the value:
\[
f \approx \frac{1}{2\pi \sqrt{2 \times 10^{-16}}} \approx \frac{1}{2\pi \times 1.414 \times 10^{-8}} \approx \SI{1.78e7}{\hertz}
\]

\subsection*{(b) Wavelength of the Waves}

The wavelength \( \lambda \) is related to the frequency \( f \) and the speed of light \( c \) by:
\[
\lambda = \frac{c}{f}
\]
where \( c = \SI{3e8}{\meter\per\second} \).

Substituting the calculated frequency:
\[
\lambda = \frac{3 \times 10^8 \, \si{\meter\per\second}}{1.78 \times 10^7 \, \si{\hertz}} \approx \SI{16.85}{\meter}
\]

\end{document}

