\[
\delta = \sqrt{\frac{2}{\mu_0 \sigma \omega}}
\]

where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \(\mu_0\) is the permeability of free space,
    \item \(\sigma\) is the conductivity of the material, and
    \item \(\omega\) is the angular frequency of the wave.
\end{itemize}

To find the conductivity \(\sigma\), use the relation:
\[
\sigma = \frac{1}{\rho}
\]

The angular frequency \(\omega\) is related to the wavelength \(\lambda\) by:
\[
\omega = \frac{2\pi c}{\lambda}
\]

where \(c\) is the speed of light in vacuum.

Substituting these into the expression for \(\delta\), we can estimate the skin depth.

\end{document}

