\sigma = (\SI{8.85e-12}{\farad\per\meter}) \times 6 \times \SI{2e3}{\volt\per\meter}
\]

Calculating this gives:

\[
\sigma = \SI{1.062e-7}{\coulomb\per\meter\squared}
\]

Thus, the surface charge density induced on the face is approximately \SI{1.062e-7}{\coulomb\per\meter\squared}.

