\begin{document}

To calculate the wave and group velocities of the TE\(_{01}\) mode in a rectangular waveguide, we need to use the following formulas:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Wave velocity (\(v_p\))}:
    \[
    v_p = \frac{c}{\sqrt{1 - \left(\frac{f_c}{f}\right)^2}}
    \]

    \item \textbf{Group velocity (\(v_g\))}:
    \[
    v_g = c \sqrt{1 - \left(\frac{f_c}{f}\right)^2}
    \]
\end{enumerate}

where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \(c\) is the speed of light in vacuum (\(c \approx 3 \times 10^8 \, \text{m/s}\)),
    \item \(f\) is the operating frequency,
    \item \(f_c\) is the cutoff frequency for the TE\(_{01}\) mode.
\end{itemize}

The cutoff frequency \(f_c\) for the TE\(_{mn}\) mode in a rectangular waveguide is given by:
\[
f_c = \frac{c}{2} \sqrt{\left(\frac{m}{a}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{n}{b}\right)^2}
\]

For the TE\(_{01}\) mode, \(m = 0\) and \(n = 1\), and the dimensions of the waveguide are \(a = 1 \, \text{cm} = 0.01 \, \text{m}\) and \(b = 2 \, \text{cm} = 0.02 \, \text{m}\). Thus, the cutoff frequency becomes:
\[
f_c = \frac{c}{2} \cdot \frac{1}{b} = \frac{3 \times 10^8}{2 \times 0.02} = 7.5 \times 10^9 \, \text{Hz}
\]

Substitute \(f_c\) into the equations for \(v_p\) and \(v_g\) to find the wave and group velocities at a given frequency \(f\).

\end{document}

