\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{graphicx}

\begin{document}

\section*{Interference Pattern from Two Slits}

A beam of monochromatic light with wavelength $\lambda$ is incident upon two slits $S_1$ and $S_2$ a distance $d$ apart, as shown in Fig. 15.11. We derive an expression, in terms of $\lambda$, $L$, $d$, and $m$, for the distance $y_m$ from the central point to the $m$-th bright fringe of the interference pattern on a screen a distance $L$ away when $L \gg y_m$.

\subsection*{Derivation of the Expression}

For constructive interference (bright fringes), the path difference between the light from the two slits must be an integer multiple of the wavelength:

\begin{equation}
d \sin \theta_m = m \lambda
\end{equation}

where $m$ is the order of the fringe (an integer), $\theta_m$ is the angle to the $m$-th bright fringe, and $d$ is the slit separation.

For small angles, $\sin \theta_m \approx \tan \theta_m = \frac{y_m}{L}$, thus:

\begin{equation}
d \frac{y_m}{L} = m \lambda
\end{equation}

Solving for $y_m$, we get:

\begin{equation}
y_m = \frac{m \lambda L}{d}
\end{equation}

\subsection*{Calculation of Fringe Spacing}

Given:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Slit separation, $d = 2 \, \text{mm} = 2 \times 10^{-3} \, \text{m}$
    \item Wavelength, $\lambda = 612 \, \text{nm} = 612 \times 10^{-9} \, \text{m}$
    \item Distance to screen, $L = 4 \, \text{m}$
\end{itemize}

The spacing between adjacent bright fringes (fringe spacing, $\Delta y$) is given by:

\begin{equation}
\Delta y = y_{m+1} - y_m = \frac{(m+1) \lambda L}{d} - \frac{m \lambda L}{d} = \frac{\lambda L}{d}
\end{equation}

Substituting the given values:

\begin{equation}
\Delta y = \frac{612 \times 10^{-9} \, \text{m} \times 4 \, \text{m}}{2 \times 10^{-3} \, \text{m}}
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
\Delta y = 1.224 \times 10^{-3} \, \text{m} = 1.224 \, \text{mm}
\end{equation}

Thus, the spacing of the fringes observed on the screen is $1.224 \, \text{mm}$.

\begin{figure}[h]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{fig15_11.png}
    \caption{Diagram of the double-slit experiment setup.}
    \label{fig:15_11}
\end{figure}

\end{document}

