\]

Finally, solve for the base length \( L \):
\[
L = \frac{R}{\left| \frac{d n}{d \lambda} \right|} = \frac{0.001018}{6.96 \times 10^{-6}} \approx 146.26 \, \text{cm}
\]

Thus, the length of the base of the prism required to resolve the sodium lines is approximately \SI{146.26}{\centi\meter}.

\end{document}

